Metadata: Additional records for "Callianassa rathbunae" Schmitt, 1935, from Florida and the Bahamas (Crustacea: Decapoda: Callianassidae)
"Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington," 99(2):347-349, 1986.

The mud shrimp "Callianassa rathbunae" Schmitt is far more abundant in shallow water habitats than suggested by records in the literature. More than 40 specimens are recorded from localities in the Bahamas and the Indian River, Florida.
